    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Very large cylindrical beakers or steins, usually made of glass but also ceramic or metal, often decorated with enamel or engraving. They were used for drinking beer and wine, made in Germany from the 16th century onwards. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
